  • Constructor Details

    • Crime

      public Crime​(java.lang.String id, java.time.LocalDateTime date, java.lang.String block, java.lang.String iucr, java.lang.String primaryDescription, java.lang.String secondaryDescription, java.lang.String locationDescription, java.lang.Boolean arrest, java.lang.Boolean domestic, java.lang.Integer beat, java.lang.Integer ward, java.lang.String fbiCD, java.lang.Integer xCoord, java.lang.Integer yCoord, java.lang.Double latitude, java.lang.Double longitude)
      Initializes a crime object.
      Parameters:
      date - A required field which contains the year, month, day and time of the crime
      block - An optional field which contains what block the crime occurred in
      iucr - An optional field which contains the Illinois Uniform Crime Reporting number
      primaryDescription - A required field which contains the primary description of the crime
      secondaryDescription - A required field which contains the more descriptive secondary description of the crime
      locationDescription - An optional field which contains the description of the location where the crime occurred
      arrest - An optional field which contains whether the crime resulted in an arrest
      domestic - An optional field which contains if the crime was domestic
      beat - An optional field which contains the beat.
      ward - An optional field which contains the ward.
      fbiCD - An optional field which contains FBI crime code.
      xCoord - An optional field which is has the x-coordinate of where the crime occurred
      yCoord - An optional field which is has the y-coordinate of where the crime occurred
      latitude - An optional field which is has the latitude of where the crime occurred
      longitude - An optional field which is has the longitude of where the crime occurred
